    "content": "<h1>DAY’S JOURNEY</h1><p>A way of estimating distances in Bible times. A day’s journey was about 32.2&nbsp;kilometers (20 miles) but depended on such things as the mode of travel, the terrain, and the weather. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:18\">Exodus 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:31\">Numbers 11:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:4\">1&nbsp;Kings 19:4</a>, and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:44\">Luke 2:44 </a>all mention a day&apos;s journey.<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:44\"> </a></p><p>Scripture also refers to a Sabbath day’s journey (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:12\">Acts 1:12</a>). A Sabbath day’s journey was probably about one kilometer (3500 feet). </p><p><em>See</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"7248\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Sabbath Day’s Journey</span>.</p>",
